randomiser-instance.name: DatesTill2010
randomiser-instance.description: A simple date generator which generates date starting from 1970-01-01 until the year 2010. When entering dates in From, To fields, the date should follow the format YYYY-MM-DD. You can change how the date appears using the date format

randomiser-instance.name: EnglishFirstnames
randomiser-instance.description: The value of the seed is used to synchronise this generator with the emails generator. If you provide the same firstname seed in the emails generator, the emails generator will generate emails that contain part of the firstname that the EnglishFirstnames generator generates.

randomiser-instance.name: EnglishLastnames
randomiser-instance.description: The value of the seed is used to synchronise this generator with the emails generator. If you provide the same firstname seed in the emails generator, the emails generator will generate emails that contain part of the last name that the EnglishLastnames generator generates.

randomiser-instance.name: EnglishWords
randomiser-instance.description: I had to develop this generator when I realised that I did not really like the EnglishTextRandomiser which tends to cut-off the last few letters.

randomiser-instance.name: EmailSynch
randomiser-instance.description: Notice this instance of EmailRandomiser will be in sync with EnglishFirstnames and EnglishLastnames. This means that the generator here will actually generate emails that use the first name and the last name the other two generators have generated. This is achieved by using the same dictionaries and generating the same "random" sequence of choices.

randomiser-instance.name: EnglishText2
randomiser-instance.description:
An example of using a generator.panels.PanelGenericRandomiser; instead of building a panel for a new generator, you can use the PanelGenericRandomiser which allows you to set a value for any key. In this example, this panel is used for the EnglishTextRandomiserGeneric (which is the same as EnglishTextRandomiser).
Simply set the keys-values that the EnglishTextRandomiser needs - of course you need to know what these keys are for each Randomiser, but the idea is that this Panel is used for quick and dirty testing of a new Randomiser. NO V
